<subSubSection id="329992E299F9296D45FF506BB5D1A1A0" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" type="nomenclatural note">
<paragraph id="099310161DA006C0C54C6C5953FA47CB" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Nomenclatural note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D5FA0FB9C8814F01C857693444E8F1C9" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName id="703F50AC3FC4C418AC1733847BBE8EEE" authorityName="Francisco &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pachyptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachyptera linearis" order="Lamiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="C6036B1DB3442FA382CD215D4F23CD6B" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Pachyptera linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a new species described here based on new morphological and molecular phylogenetic data (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AF873991553A126D63EB9EE618ACB5ED" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Schematic diagram summarising phylogenetic relationships within Pachyptera, with morphological characters mapped on the diagram. Names of the terminal taxa indicate the taxon in which these species were previously included. The taxonomic updates proposed here are also indicated. Relationships depicted follow Francisco and Lohmann (submitted)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.92.20987.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/180438" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">1</figureCitation>
; Francisco and Lohmann submitted). The best quality material was selected as the holotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5B4C06A20C36F67FC0FC267872F53913" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" type="taxonomic comments">
<paragraph id="31F40B4AD29952C24D69F4AC0B26DFAE" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Taxonomic comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EB91C3109D540BDEC0162E68D79C5560" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName id="D7AD108BBF7BD91987D71A79749E98F0" authorityName="Francisco &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pachyptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachyptera linearis" order="Lamiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="7B3D0DD0853F6930C48BFD92A1E4D615" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Pachyptera linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by white and infundibuliform corollas, with a sparsely pubescent and sparsely lepidote ovary. Furthermore, the capsule is linear, flattened, coriaceous to woody, with an inconspicuous longitudinal midline on the valves. The seeds are oblong, thin, coriaceous to woody, winged, with short membranaceous or coriaceous and hyaline wings. 
<taxonomicName id="2D9913B6ADE1482E1AB071D4C1E62357" authorityName="Francisco &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Pachyptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachyptera linearis" order="Lamiales" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="DF2B0E35E8EB69CA01403F17A70F283D" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Pachyptera linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the white infundibuliform flowers with its sister species 
<taxonomicName id="28AFEDA72CE11F8CF560F213CBB6021C" genus="P." lsidName="P. kerere" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" rank="species" species="kerere">
<emphasis id="5F0C78D62ABFAAFB2E5E58BB4E0FD9E1" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">P. kerere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="859250970A3C280A635C5814E5999FE5" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Schematic diagram summarising phylogenetic relationships within Pachyptera, with morphological characters mapped on the diagram. Names of the terminal taxa indicate the taxon in which these species were previously included. The taxonomic updates proposed here are also indicated. Relationships depicted follow Francisco and Lohmann (submitted)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.92.20987.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/180438" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">1</figureCitation>
). Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName id="EE2B81EF948594A5460CC7DF4546460E" genus="P." lsidName="P. linearis" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="C4B55383C8D98AD1F242971D1F52A42B" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">P. linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguible from 
<taxonomicName id="1128C63ECC1AFE28AA3DDB83587B40F2" genus="P." lsidName="P. kerere" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" rank="species" species="kerere">
<emphasis id="D5459C628D555D5E78F179094B2DAA7F" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">P. kerere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the fruit morphology.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
